<h3>Research &gt; Online Resources  &gt; Seniors</h3>


<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul class="resource_list">
<li><a href="https://www.aarp.org/work/"><strong>AARP Work &amp; Retirement</strong></a> &ndash; A  nonprofit organization for people 50 and older. Includes articles about job  hunting, working after retirement, and budgeting and saving.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.aagponline.org/" target="_blank"><strong>American  Association for Geriatric Psychiatry</strong></a> &ndash; Information  for both caregivers and care recipients; includes depression and dementia fact  sheets, resources for caregivers, and the latest caregiver research.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.warrenville.il.us/index.aspx?nid=413" title="https://www.warrenville.il.us/liv_sen_main.aspx"><strong>City of Warrenville - Seniors</strong></a> &ndash; City of Warrenville services for  Seniors, including transportation and  utility assistance.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.aarp.org/home-garden/transportation/driver_safety/?cmp=RDRCT-DRIVE"><strong>Driver  Safety Program for Seniors</strong></a> &ndash; AARP's Driver Safety Program is  designed for driver&rsquo;s aged 50 and over. Classes are offered locally, search at  this site. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.dupagehousing.org/"><strong>DuPage Housing Authority</strong></a> &ndash; Program providing rental assistance to income-eligible families and  individuals, the elderly and persons with disabilities. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.dupageseniorcouncil.org/"><strong>DuPage Senior Citizens Council</strong></a> &ndash; Initiates, delivers, monitors and  coordinates services, which promote the ability of older persons to live their  lives in dignity. Also offers a senior nutrition program and home maintenance  program. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.eldercare.gov/Eldercare.NET/Public/Index.aspx"><strong>Eldercare  Locator</strong></a> &ndash; By entering a zip code, caregivers and older persons  can locate local information and referral organizations. These organizations  can help them locate appropriate services. Provided by the U.S. Administration  on Aging.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.caregiver.org"><strong>Family  Caregiver Alliance Resource Center</strong></a> &ndash; Provides information on a variety of caregiving resources; 40+ fact  sheets (some in Spanish and Chinese); online support groups and care planning  consultation, and policy alerts.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.cbrx.il.gov/"><strong>Illinois Circuit Breaker &amp;  Illinois Cares Rx Forms</strong></a> &ndash; Illinois Department on Aging's Circuit  Breaker program provides grants to senior citizens and persons with  disabilities to help them reduce the impact of taxes and prescription  medications on their lives.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.state.il.us/aging/" title="https://www.state.il.us/aging/"><strong>Illinois Department on Aging</strong></a> &ndash; A source of services provided by the  State of Illinois for Seniors, including a Directory of Agencies serving  seniors, Illinois Circuit Breaker, grandparents raising grandchildren,  caregiver support, and much more. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.medicare.gov/campaigns/caregiver/caregiver.html"><strong>Medicare  for Caregivers</strong></a> &ndash; This site includes a directory of participating  physicians, comparison of supplemental insurance plans, and data from Nursing  Home Compare. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.metrofamily.org/"><strong>Metropolitan Family Services</strong></a> &ndash; Provides and mobilizes services needed to strengthen families and communities  through multiple partnerships. Senior and caregiver support services, violence  prevention programs, counseling, mental health services, financial literacy. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.caregiving.org/"><strong>National Alliance for Caregiving</strong></a> &ndash; Provides  tips for caregivers, links to other caregiving resources, and the AXA Family  Foundation Family Care Resource Connection, a comprehensive database of books,  websites, and other family caregiving resources.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.benefitscheckup.org/"><strong>National Council on Aging</strong></a> &ndash; Lists more  than 1,000 federal and state assistance programs for older adults. An online  questionnaire helps the user identify what programs he or she may be entitled  to, along with instructions on how to apply for them. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.needymeds.org/"><strong>Needy Meds</strong></a> &ndash; Needy Meds  lists pharmaceutical companies that offer programs to assist patients unable to  buy necessary medicines.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.ageguide.org/"><strong>Northeastern  Illinois Area Agency on Aging</strong></a> &ndash; Information for both caregivers and care recipients. Includes  information on local resources in northeastern Illinois for the National Family  Caregiver Support Program and links to state and national resources.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.medicare.gov/NHCompare/Include/DataSection/Questions/SearchCriteria.asp?version=default&browser=Firefox%7C2%7CWin2000&language=English&defaultstatus=0&pagelist=Home&CookiesEnabledStatus=True"><strong>Nursing Home Compare</strong></a> &ndash; Provides  detailed information about the past performance of every Medicare and Medicaid  certified nursing home in the country. Also includes a Guide to Choosing a  Nursing Home and a Nursing Home Checklist to help with nursing home choices.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.retiredbrains.com/Home/default.aspx"><strong>RetiredBrains</strong></a> &ndash; Information on creating and updating  resumes, as well as job postings. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.dupageco.org/seniorsvcs" title="https://www.dupageco.org/seniorsvcs"><strong>Senior  Citizens Resource Directory</strong></a> &ndash; A source providing information on services for seniors in DuPage County, including  elderabuse, home delivered meals, transportation, housing and a lot more.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.illinois.gov/aging/AboutUs/Pages/employ.aspx"><strong>Senior Community Service Employment  Program</strong></a> &ndash; Offers placement, counseling and  training to people 55 and older who are entering or re-entering the job market.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.seniorhomesharing.org/"><strong>Senior Home  Sharing</strong></a> &ndash; Provides a shared senior lifestyle through the creation of  group homes where seniors live together as a family with private bedrooms for  six or seven seniors. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.dupageco.org/Community_Services/Senior_Services/1699/"><strong>Senior Resource  Directory</strong></a> &ndash; Listings of resources for those ages 60 and over. Published by DuPage County Senior Services.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.seniorjournal.com/index.html" title="https://www.seniorjournal.com/index.html"><strong>SeniorJournal.com</strong></a> &ndash; Daily news and information just  for seniors online, includes the latest tips on medicine, social security,  Medicare, fitness, politics and much more. </li>

<li><a href="https://www.caregiver.com/"><strong>Today&rsquo;s Caregiver</strong></a> &ndash; Offers care  tips, links to local and national resources, online discussions, and articles  from the magazine <em>Today's Caregiver</em>.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.wellspouse.org/"><strong>Well Spouse</strong></a> &ndash; Provides  spouses of the frail elderly with a virtual support community, including  message boards and live Internet chats with other spouse caregivers. Links to  disease-specific Internet sites are also highlighted.</li>

<li><a href="https://www.wiredseniors.com/" title="https://www.wiredseniors.com/"><strong>Wired Seniors</strong></a> &ndash; A website providing information  on seniors' discount mail, seniors helping seniors, a home exchange, seniors&rsquo;  radio, and much more. </li>
</ul>
